Unfortunately the spelling of 'Gerard' left a lot to be desired, but the Liverpool captain appreciated the tribute.

Gerrard was back in action for Liverpool in their 1-0 win over Swansea after missing the last seven games with a hamstring injury.

Jordan Henderson's second-half goal was enough to earn Brendan Rodgers' side a victory that drew them within two points of fourth-placed Manchester United in the race for Champions League football. 

